<section xml:id="C18.S22">
<title>Hahn Class: Recurrence Relations and Differences</title>        
 
<subsection xml:id="C18.S22.SS1">
<title>Recurrence Relations in <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C18.S22.SS1.m1">n</Math></title>        
  
<paragraph xml:id="C18.S22.Px1">
<title>Hahn</title>   
<para xml:id="C18.S22.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C18.S22.Px1.p1.s1">
With <Math equation-number="18.22.1" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S22.E1">p_{n}(x)=Q_{n}\left(x;\alpha,\beta,N\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="18.22.2" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S22.E2">-xp_{n}(x)=A_{n}p_{n+1}(x)-\left(A_{n}+C_{n}\right)p_{n}(x)+C_{n}p_{n-1}(x),</Math> where <Math equation-number="18.22.3" mode="display" xml:id="C18.S22.E3">A_{n}=\frac{(n+\alpha+\beta+1)(n+\alpha+1)(N-n)}{(2n+\alpha+\beta+1)(2n+\alpha +\beta+2)},C_{n}=\frac{n(n+\alpha+\beta+N+1)(n+\beta)}{(2n+\alpha+\beta)(2n+\alpha+\beta+ 1)}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</paragraph>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C18.S22.Px2">
<title>Krawtchouk, Meixner, and Charlier</title>  
 
